{
  "texts": [
    "Guidance to develop AI ethically and responsibly may need to shift to a proactive and operationally strategic approach for practical development instead of remaining prescriptive.Within the frameworks that guide AI's development, the question remains: Who is in charge or responsible for ethically aligning AI in healthcare?",
    "Empirical evidence suggests that development teams are often more concerned with the usefulness and viability of the product rather than its ethical aspects [35].",
    "In part, these results are expected as software developers are not responsible for strategic decisions regarding how and why AI is developed [17].",
    "While some academics have suggested embedding ethics into AI's design by integrating ethicists in the development team [36], management (including product managers) may be a better entry point to ensure that AI is ethically developed from its initial ideation.",
    "In a survey, AI developers felt capable of designing pro-ethical AI, but the question remained whether they were responsible for these decisions [37]."
  ]
}